{"title_page": "2000 FIFA Futsal World Championship", "text_new": "{{Infobox international football competition\n| tourney_name = \n| year = 2000\n| other_titles = FIFA Futsal World Championship Guatemala 2000<br>Campeonato Mundial de f\u00fatbol sala de la FIFA 2000\n| image = 2000 FIFA Futsal World Championship.jpg\n| size = 150px\n| caption = \n| country = Guatemala\n| dates = 18 November \u2013 3 December\n| num_teams = 16\n| confederations = 6\n| venues = 2\n| cities = 1\n| champion_other = {{futsal|ESP}}\n| count = 1\n| second_other = {{futsal|BRA}}\n| third_other = {{futsal|POR}}\n| fourth_other = {{futsal|RUS}}\n| matches = 40\n| goals = 302\n| attendance = 224038\n| top_scorer = {{flagicon|BRA}} [[Manoel Tobias]] (19 goals)\n| player = {{flagicon|BRA}} [[Manoel Tobias]]\n| prevseason =  [[1996 FIFA Futsal World Championship|1996]]\n| nextseason = [[2004 FIFA Futsal World Championship|2004]]\n}}\n\nThe '''2000 FIFA Futsal World Championship''' was the fourth [[FIFA Futsal World Cup|FIFA Futsal World Championship]], the quadrennial international [[futsal]] championship contested by the men's national teams of the member associations of [[FIFA]]. It was held between 18 November and 3 December 2000 in [[Guatemala]]. It was the first FIFA tournament held in the country.\n\n[[Spain national futsal team|Spain]] won the tournament, defeating [[Brazil national futsal team|Brazil]] in the final. They ended a streak of three straight championships by Brazil and also became the only nation other than the South Americans to win the title at that time.\n\n== Qualifying criteria ==\n\n{{main|2000 FIFA Futsal World Championship qualification}}\n\n=== Qualified nations ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" width=\"800\"\n|-\n! Competition !! Date !! Venue !! Berths !! Qualified\n|-\n| Host Nation || colspan=\"2\"|&nbsp; || align=\"center\"|1 || {{futsal|Guatemala}}\n|-\n| [[2000 AFC Futsal Championship]] || May 5\u201312, 2000 || {{THA}}|| align=\"center\"| 3 || {{futsal|IRN}} <br/> 