ive/guatemala2000/index.html FIFA Futsal World Championship Guatemala 2000], FIFA.com\n*[https://www.fifa.com/mm/document/afdeveloping/technicaldevp/50/05/21/futsal_00_tr_gua_169.pdf FIFA Technical Report]\n\n{{FIFA Futsal World Cup}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:2000 Fifa Futsal World Championship}}\n[[Category:FIFA Futsal World Cup]]\n[[Category:2000 FIFA Futsal World Championship| ]]\n[[Category:2000 in futsal|Fifa Futsal World Championship, 2000]]\n[[Category:2000\u201301 in Guatemalan football|Fifa Futsal World Championship, 2000]]\n[[Category:International futsal competitions hosted by Guatemala]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox international football competition\n| tourney_name = \n| year = 2000\n| other_titles = FIFA Futsal World Championship Guatemala 2000<br>Campeonato Mundial de f\u00fatbol sala de la FIFA 2000\n| image = 2000 FIFA Futsal World Championship.jpg\n| size = 150px\n| caption = \n| country = Guatemala\n| dates = 18 November \u2013 3 December\n| num_teams = 16\n| confederations = 6\n| venues = 2\n| cities = 1\n| champion_other = {{futsal|ESP}}\n| count = 1\n| second_other = {{futsal|BRA}}\n| third_other = {{futsal|POR}}\n| fourth_other = {{futsal|RUS}}\n| matches = 40\n| goals = 302\n| attendance = 224038\n| top_scorer = {{flagicon|BRA}} [[Manoel Tobias]] (19 goals)\n| player = {{flagicon|BRA}} [[Manoel Tobias]]\n| prevseason =  [[1996 FIFA Futsal World Championship|1996]]\n| nextseason = [[2004 FIFA Futsal World Championship|2004]]\n}}\n\nThe '''2000 FIFA Futsal World Championship''' was the fourth [[FIFA Futsal World Cup|FIFA Futsal World Championship]], the quadrennial international [[futsal]] championship contested by the men's national teams of the member associations of [[FIFA]]. It was held between 18 November and 3 December 2000 in [[Guatemala]]. It was the first FIFA tournament held in the country.\n\n[[Spain national futsal team|Spain]] won the tournament, defeating [[Brazil national futsal team|Brazil]] in the final. They ended a streak of three straight championships by Brazil and also became the only nation other than the South Americans to win the title at that time.\n\n== Qualifying criteria ==\n\n{{main|2000 FIFA Futsal World Championship qualification}}\n\n=== Qualified nations ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" width=\"800\"\n|-\n! Competition !! Date !! Venue !! Berths !! Qualified\n|-\n| Host Nation || colspan=\"2\"|&nbsp; || align=\"center\"|1 || {{futsal|Guatemala}}\n|-\n| [[2000 AFC Futsal Championship]] || May 5\u201312, 2000 || {{THA}}|| align=\"center\"| 3 || {{futsal|IRN}} <br/> {{futsal|THA}} <br/> {{futsal|Kazakhstan}}\n|-\n| [[2000 African Futsal Championship]] || April 16\u201321, 2000 || {{EGY}} || align=\"center\"|1 || {{futsal|EGY}}\n|-\n| [[2000 CONCACAF Futsal Championship]] || July 20\u201329, 2000 || {{GUA}} || align=\"center\"|2 || {{futsal|Costa Rica}} <br/> {{futsal|CUB}} \n|- \n| [[2000 CONMEBOL Futsal Championship|2000 South American Futsal Championship]] || April 29 \u2013 May 7, 2000 || {{BRA}} || align=\"center\"|3 || {{futsal|URU}} <br/> {{futsal|ARG}} <br/> {{futsal|BRA}}\n|-\n| [[1999 Oceanian Futsal Championship]] || August 21\u201328, 1999 || {{flagicon|Vanuatu}} [[Vanuatu]] || align=\"center\"|1 || {{futsal|Australia}}\n|-\n| [[2000 FIFA Futsal World Cup qualification (UEFA)|UEFA Preliminary Competition]] || January 30 \u2013 March 5, 2000 || Groups || align=\"center\"|5 || {{futsal|POR}} <br/> {{futsal|Spain}} <br/> {{futsal|Russia}} <br/> {{futsal|Croatia}} <br/> {{futsal|Netherlands}} \n|-\n! TOTAL !! colspan=\"2\"| !! 16 !! Field is Finalized\n|}\n\n== Venues ==\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n! colspan=2|[[Guatemala City]]\n|-\n| [[Domo Polideportivo de la CDAG]]<br>Capacity: 10,000\n| Gimnasio Nacional Teodoro Palacios Flores<br>Capacity: 8,000\n|}\n\n==Squads==\n{{Main|2000 FIFA Futsal World Championship squads}}\nEach nation submitted a squad of 14 players, including two or three goalkeepers.\n\n==First round==\n\n===Group A===\n(18 November - 23